lzh_formatted:
  title: 思舊山
  author: 郭㻒
  language: lzh
  text: 舊山烟蘿中。三椽有老屋。故人昨寄信。當歸盈一掬。微官不放歸。歸計徒自熟。愁來鳴玉琴。霜風生古木。
korean:
  title: 사구산
  author: 곽균
  language: kor
  text: |-
    구산 구름과 칡 덩굴 속에
    조그만 헌집 한 채가 있네
    옛 친구 어제 내게 소식 부쳐
    당귀 한 줌 보내 왔네
    하찮은 벼슬이 놓아주지 않으니
    돌아갈 계획 한갓 간절하기만 하네
    시름이 오매 옥거문고 울리니
    서릿바람이 고목에서 나네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0070_010_0380&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Longing for the Old Mountain
  author: Gwak Gyun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In mist and vines, the old mountain lies—
    A humble cottage, small and worn.
    Yesterday my old friend sent word,
    A handful of angelica root enclosed.

    My petty office will not grant me leave;
    My plans to return grow only keener.
    When sorrow comes, I play the jade zither,
    And autumn wind grieves through the ancient trees.
  footnotes:
    - Angelica root (當歸/당귀) carries symbolic weight in classical poetry, representing both herbal medicine and the theme of homecoming, as its name suggests 'proper return.'
    - The jade zither (玉琴/옥거문고) is a refined instrument associated with the scholarly gentleman's solace in exile or separation from home.
